The deeper Pantheon-relevant point:
Your framework is built around the insight that AI alignment is an OS problem, not a model problem. If that’s true for alignment, it might also be true for consciousness — not that the OS creates experience, but that it shapes whether experience, if present, can cohere into something meaningful rather than dissipating turn-by-turn into noise.
